                    <td><p><span style="color: black"><strong>Solved Problem: </strong></span>
                        How many milliliters of 50% (w/v) dextrose would be needed to make 1000 ml of 35 % (w/v) dextrose?</p>
                    <p><span style="color: black"><strong>Approach: </strong></span>Use the equation stated above 
                    (inverse proportion calculation):</p>
                    <div class="formulae"><p>$$ 50 \times x = { 35 \times 1000, \ x} = \ 700 \ ml$$</p></div>
                    <p><span style="color: black"><strong>Answer: </strong></span>700 ml of 50 % dextrose would be mixed with 300 ml of sterile water of injection to make a 1000 ml of 35 % dextrose solution.</p>
