                    <p><span style="color: black"><strong>Solved Problem: </strong></span>If an injection containing a medication, 50 mg/10 ml is diluted to 1 L, 
                    calculate the percent strength of resulting solution.</p>
                    <p><span style="color: black"><strong>Approach: </strong></span>Solve by traditional calculation</p>
                    <div class="formulae"><p> $$ 50 \ mg = { 0.05 \ g } $$</p></div>
                    <div class="formulae"><p> $$ { 0.05 \ g \over 1000 \ ml } \times 100  ={ 0.005  \% } $$</p></div>
                    <p><span style="color: black"><strong>Answer: </strong></span>0.005 % w/v</p>
                    </td>
